in many different areas.

527
00:57:44,400 --> 00:57:45,230
Hmm.

528
00:57:45,250 --> 00:57:48,890
And Mr. Stop supports our
research in premature birth.

529
00:57:48,920 --> 00:57:50,810
So, do you see each other socially?

530
00:57:51,820 --> 00:57:54,310
Yeah, well, that depends
on how you mean.

531
00:57:54,350 --> 00:57:56,190
It's quite simple, actually.
Do you have friends in common?

532
00:57:56,390 --> 00:57:59,150
Yes, we-we mix in the same circles, so.

533
00:57:59,230 --> 00:58:00,600
W-why are you uh...

534
00:58:00,630 --> 00:58:01,500
To know if you were...

535
00:58:01,530 --> 00:58:04,200
Have you ever practiced in other
parts of the country, Dr. Vetlesen?

536
00:58:04,220 --> 00:58:07,800
Yes, I have in Eidsvoll,
in uh, Lillehammer.

537
00:58:07,830 --> 00:58:09,340
I see you have a picture of
Mon Plaisir pavilion...

538
00:58:09,400 --> 00:58:11,570
- in Bergen.
- Yes, yes, in Bergen.

539
00:58:13,230 --> 00:58:14,900
Do you live alone?

540
00:58:16,650 --> 00:58:19,280
Yes, I uh, I am a reluctant bachelor.

541
00:58:19,360 --> 00:58:21,420
Is there anyone
in the house right now?

542
00:58:23,460 --> 00:58:26,240
Because I thought I saw someone
in the window when I passed.

543
00:58:27,700 --> 00:58:32,070
Well, if you want to take a look around,
I will need to see a search warrant.

544
00:58:32,090 --> 00:58:34,680
In fact, if you don't mind,

545
00:58:34,700 --> 00:58:36,800
I would like to call my lawyer...

546
00:58:37,080 --> 00:58:39,360
before I answer any more
of your questions.

547
00:58:39,440 --> 00:58:41,570
That won't be necessary,
Dr. Vetlesen.

548
00:58:43,000 --> 00:58:45,280
You can bring your lawyer
when we see you next time.

549
00:58:50,780 --> 00:58:52,770
- Hey.
- Hi.

550
00:58:53,760 --> 00:58:54,930
What was that?

551
00:58:55,900 --> 00:58:58,530
- What?
- He isn't a suspect yet.

552
00:58:58,610 --> 00:59:00,860
We needed permission
to search the house.

553
00:59:01,020 --> 00:59:02,310
I know that.

554
00:59:02,770 --> 00:59:04,870
Why'd you ask him
about Arve Stop?

555
00:59:07,070 --> 00:59:09,200
I saw a picture
of them both together.

556
00:59:09,570 --> 00:59:10,750
And?

557
00:59:11,240 --> 00:59:13,030
And it was an innocent question.

558
00:59:13,110 --> 00:59:15,950
Jesus, anyone can see he's
trying to hide something, right?

559
00:59:34,400 --> 00:59:36,680
Cloudberry.

560
00:59:39,780 --> 00:59:41,910
If you hadn't told me
to look out for it,

561
00:59:41,940 --> 00:59:44,330
I'd have assumed she was
attached to his security detail.

562
00:59:44,360 --> 00:59:45,570
Cloudberry?

563
00:59:45,600 --> 00:59:47,510
It's her password.

564
00:59:50,000 --> 00:59:53,530
<i>Does this strike you as the
proper time and place for this?</i>

565
00:59:58,820 --> 01:00:00,530
Arve Stop.

566
01:00:00,560 --> 01:00:01,480
<i>Idiot.</i>

567
01:00:01,510 --> 01:00:04,480
She filmed him at rallies...

568
01:00:04,570 --> 01:00:07,740
at restaurants, at home.

569
01:00:27,150 --> 01:00:28,510
Hi.

570
01:00:29,950 --> 01:00:31,660
Do you want a ride?

571
01:00:33,690 --> 01:00:34,690
No.

572
01:00:44,850 --> 01:00:46,270
Bye.

573
01:01:43,640 --> 01:01:47,800
<i>The 8:45 train to Bergen
leaving on platform five.</i>

574
01:01:49,490 --> 01:01:50,720
Oh, sorry.

575
01:01:53,800 --> 01:01:56,420
<i>This is the 8:45
service to Bergen</i>

576
01:01:56,440 --> 01:01:59,770
<i>which stops in Gol,
Finse, Voss and Bergen.</i>

577
01:02:00,270 --> 01:02:03,090
<i>The next station is Gol.</i>

578
01:02:21,620 --> 01:02:23,040
Hi, Harry.

579
01:02:25,830 --> 01:02:26,900
Hi.

580
01:02:27,040 --> 01:02:28,870
Hiding in the playroom, are we?

581
01:02:28,900 --> 01:02:29,970
Yes.

582
01:02:31,510 --> 01:02:34,130
Don't worry,
I'm getting off at the next stop.

583
01:02:35,670 --> 01:02:37,000
Going far?

584
01:02:37,020 --> 01:02:38,140
Bergen.

585
01:02:38,240 --> 01:02:40,440
Ah, rather you than me.

586
01:02:40,710 --> 01:02:43,900
Then again, I'm attending
a three-day conference on

587
01:02:43,930 --> 01:02:46,450
bio-identical hormone restoration.

588
01:02:46,510 --> 01:02:48,810
I thought you were a plastic surgeon?

589
01:02:48,970 --> 01:02:50,120
Well, you know...

590
01:02:50,150 --> 01:02:53,510
Cosmetic surgery needs
to move with the times, too.

591
01:02:54,240 --> 01:02:57,420
We're swapping the scalpel
for hormone replacement therapy.

592
01:02:58,990 --> 01:03:01,110
If you can slow down
the aging process...

593
01:03:01,130 --> 01:03:03,200
there won't be any
need for face-lifts, will there?

594
01:03:03,800 --> 01:03:06,260
I'll bear that in mind.

595
01:03:08,710 --> 01:03:10,750
So, how's the prescription working?

596
01:03:12,260 --> 01:03:13,750
Sleeping like a baby.

597
01:03:14,240 --> 01:03:15,430
Splendid.

598
01:03:16,840 --> 01:03:20,770
So, you, you canceled the Oleg thing?

599
01:03:23,150 --> 01:03:24,900
The school trip?

600
01:03:25,000 --> 01:03:26,750
Weren't you supposed to...

601
01:03:26,900 --> 01:03:28,540
Oh, shit.

602
01:03:31,320 --> 01:03:33,120
- Shit!
- I'm sorry, Harry, uh...

603
01:03:33,140 --> 01:03:35,050
- I'm sure he's fine.
- Oleg, you coming?

604
01:03:35,070 --> 01:03:36,250
Come on.

605
01:03:36,270 --> 01:03:38,350
He knows how busy you are.

606
01:03:38,400 --> 01:03:39,650
Shit.

607
01:03:41,220 --> 01:03:44,050
Look, look, y-you're
not his father, Harry.

608
01:03:45,130 --> 01:03:46,640
What does that mean?

609
01:03:47,350 --> 01:03:48,250
Well, uh...

610
01:03:48,280 --> 01:03:50,210
I don't have to be
his father to care about him.

611
01:03:50,240 --> 01:03:51,620
I'm trying to say that...

612
01:03:51,640 --> 01:03:55,480
it's a big enough responsibility
for a real father, isn't it?

613
01:03:55,810 --> 01:03:57,660
Let alone you and me.

614
01:03:59,510 --> 01:04:00,700
I'm sorry, Harry.

615
01:04:00,730 --> 01:04:01,920
No.

616
01:04:07,850 --> 01:04:10,470
Did you hear from him?

617
01:04:10,490 --> 01:04:12,300
Why can't I go?

618
01:04:12,320 --> 01:04:13,590
Can I go with you?

619
01:04:13,610 --> 01:04:14,610
It's done!

620
01:04:17,820 --> 01:04:20,070
Hi, Oleg, it's Mathias.

621
01:04:20,640 --> 01:04:23,780
You know what, uh, I forgot to
check my messages last night, and...

622
01:04:23,800 --> 01:04:27,780
Harry called to say that
he couldn't make your trip.

623
01:04:28,490 --> 01:04:30,000
No, I know.

624
01:04:30,990 --> 01:04:34,900
No, h-he couldn't get through
to you or you mom, apparently.

625
01:04:35,690 --> 01:04:38,920
No, it's totally my fault, Oleg.

626
01:04:38,950 --> 01:04:40,820
Yes... yes... I'm sorry.

627
01:04:41,750 --> 01:04:43,190
Sorry, Oleg... yes...

628
01:04:44,950 --> 01:04:45,970
Yeah.

629
01:04:46,560 --> 01:04:51,070
So, I'll see you in a few days, then...
when I'm back from the conference.

630
01:04:55,020 --> 01:04:57,150
You didn't have to do that.

631
01:05:41,970 --> 01:05:44,050
Ready? That's it.

632
01:05:45,150 --> 01:05:47,820
Hey, Aasen, someone here
to speak to you.

633
01:05:53,150 --> 01:05:54,310
Aasen.

634
01:05:59,320 --> 01:06:02,040
My family owned
all of these buildings.

635
01:06:02,060 --> 01:06:03,550
And that house over there, too.

636
01:06:04,620 --> 01:06:06,500
Arve Stop worked for us back then.

637
01:06:06,520 --> 01:06:09,630
He was uh, bright, ambitious.

638
01:06:10,880 --> 01:06:13,160
My father really believed in him.

639
01:06:15,130 --> 01:06:18,370
The business wasn't going very well,
so we, uh, offered him a stake.

640
01:06:19,480 --> 01:06:22,300
And within a year,
he had forced us out.

641
01:06:22,320 --> 01:06:24,400
Sold the land for a fortune.

642
01:06:26,570 --> 01:06:30,320
Have any of my colleagues
been in touch with you recently?

643
01:06:30,840 --> 01:06:32,930
A young lady?

644
01:06:32,960 --> 01:06:33,950
No.

645
01:06:34,500 --> 01:06:40,260
I look at this picture now...
See Laila staring at him.

646
01:06:41,180 --> 01:06:43,230
I had no idea at the time.

647
01:06:45,180 --> 01:06:47,480
Family man, eh?

648
01:06:50,080 --> 01:06:53,330
Do you remember the name
of your wife's doctor?

649
01:06:53,650 --> 01:06:56,490
Sure. Morton Freiberg.

650
01:07:00,580 --> 01:07:04,200
Did she... ever see someone
called Vetlesen?

651
01:07:04,530 --> 01:07:06,940
Vetlesen? No.

652
01:07:06,970 --> 01:07:09,110
Dr. Idar Vetlesen.

653
01:07:12,720 --> 01:07:13,790
No.

654
01:07:15,350 --> 01:07:19,690
Any idea where I might find the
officer who's in charge of the case?

655
01:07:19,770 --> 01:07:24,980
Rafto? H-he died.

656
01:07:25,160 --> 01:07:29,350
Yeah, h-he died around
the same time.

657
01:08:14,370 --> 01:08:17,580
Detective Rafto.

658
01:08:17,600 --> 01:08:20,630
Can you connect me
to Haukeland hospital?

659
01:08:21,250 --> 01:08:23,240
What is this?
Am I under arrest?

660
01:08:23,910 --> 01:08:25,110
A cake?

661
01:08:25,130 --> 01:08:29,100
I need some information on a patient.
Laila Aasen.

662
01:08:29,580 --> 01:08:33,420
No, I don't-listen to me.
I don't know the admitting doctor.

663
01:08:33,500 --> 01:08:35,860
But perhaps she was there
for an abortion?

664
01:08:35,880 --> 01:08:37,740
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

665
01:08:37,760 --> 01:08:42,290
Well, then, I'll come down there
with a fucking warrant myself.

666
01:08:43,010 --> 01:08:46,550
♪ Happy birthday,
dear Swensson ♪

667
01:08:46,570 --> 01:08:49,530
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

668
01:08:49,550 --> 01:08:51,600
- Rafto?
- Idiot.

669
01:08:52,930 --> 01:08:55,500
Incompetent sons of...

670
01:08:56,910 --> 01:08:58,500
- Oi!
- Rafto?

671
01:08:59,660 --> 01:09:00,900
Rafto!

672
01:09:02,610 --> 01:09:04,570
What's he doing?

673
01:09:08,650 --> 01:09:09,680
Get back.

674
01:09:10,060 --> 01:09:12,120
Get back in. Get back in.

675
01:09:12,150 --> 01:09:14,410
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

676
01:09:16,140 --> 01:09:17,450
Idiot!

677
01:09:20,580 --> 01:09:22,630
I heard he was a great detective.

678
01:09:23,240 --> 01:09:25,370
He was a suicidal maniac.

679
01:09:25,650 --> 01:09:27,490
They were going to
suspend him, anyway.

680
01:09:27,650 --> 01:09:29,270
They found stuff in his drawers.

681
01:09:29,420 --> 01:09:32,420
Items he'd stolen from
various crime scenes.

682
01:09:32,950 --> 01:09:34,610
Is this him?

683
01:09:35,430 --> 01:09:37,030
Where'd you get this?

684
01:09:37,060 --> 01:09:38,670
From a colleague.

685
01:09:39,970 --> 01:09:42,220
Yes, that's him.

686
01:09:44,170 --> 01:09:46,630
He had this cabin
up on the coast.

687
01:09:46,710 --> 01:09:49,130
He used to get up there
to get smashed.

688
01:09:49,210 --> 01:09:51,720
He was probably drunk
when he shot himself.

689
01:09:55,020 --> 01:09:56,730
They look like coffee beans.

690
01:09:57,520 --> 01:09:59,570
Maybe he was trying
to sober up after all.

691
01:10:02,860 --> 01:10:04,360
You didn't check?

692
01:10:04,450 --> 01:10:07,250
The cabin was locked
from the inside.

693
01:10:07,270 --> 01:10:09,620
And he looked like that
when they found him.

694
01:10:09,650 --> 01:10:12,030
There wasn't anything
<i>to</i> check.

695
01:10:15,130 --> 01:10:16,670
Did he have any family?

696
01:10:16,880 --> 01:10:19,380
Wife who left him a year
before he killed himself. Uh...

697
01:10:20,290 --> 01:10:21,950
I think there was a daughter.

698
01:10:23,500 --> 01:10:25,340
You know where is now?

699
01:10:25,360 --> 01:10:26,630
Not a clue.

700
01:10:28,270 --> 01:10:30,520
Is the cabin still there?

701
01:10:36,580 --> 01:10:39,790
<i>What are you doing to my
fucking gun, you idiot?</i>

702
01:11:16,200 --> 01:11:17,600
Where's Harry?

703
01:11:19,260 --> 01:11:20,500
In Bergen.

704
01:12:36,720 --> 01:12:38,950
- Hello?
- Mr. Hole?

705
01:12:39,030 --> 01:12:40,630
This is Harry Hole's phone.

706
01:12:40,660 --> 01:12:42,210
Can I speak to him?

707
01:12:43,290 --> 01:12:45,790
He's not here right now, but
I can take the message for him.

708
01:12:45,910 --> 01:12:49,170
<i>Right, okay. Uh, this is Rebecca,
NRS at Telenor.</i>

709
01:12:49,190 --> 01:12:52,340
We picked up a signal from
a missing person's phone.

710
01:12:52,370 --> 01:12:53,780
Case number MP2.

711
01:12:53,800 --> 01:12:57,060
Um, I don't have any files
in front of me. Um, who's that?

712
01:12:57,060 --> 01:13:00,110
I'll check...
Birte Becker.

713
01:13:02,610 --> 01:13:05,100
- Wha... is it transmitting now?
<i>- Yeah.</i>

714
01:13:05,120 --> 01:13:06,840
Just got it in minutes ago.

715
01:13:06,860 --> 01:13:08,770
Yeah, but, w-wait,
is it moving right now?

716
01:13:08,800 --> 01:13:09,680
<i>No.</i>

717
01:13:09,700 --> 01:13:11,310
I'll send you the coordinates.

718
01:13:11,330 --> 01:13:12,890
No, just, w-what's the address?

719
01:13:12,990 --> 01:13:18,200
Uh, Parkway 1, 0139 Oslo.

720
01:13:18,220 --> 01:13:19,750
You sure that's correct?

721
01:13:19,780 --> 01:13:22,240
<i>Yes, Parkway 1.</i>

722
01:13:26,760 --> 01:13:28,490
Hey, are you all right?

723
01:15:00,160 --> 01:15:02,740
<i>This is Birte Becker.
Please leave a message.</i>

724
01:16:13,870 --> 01:16:15,970
Wednesday, unless you...

725
01:16:15,990 --> 01:16:17,140
Yes?

726
01:16:20,930 --> 01:16:22,930
- In his own garage?
- Yeah.

727
01:16:46,840 --> 01:16:49,380
Ah, the great Harry Hole.

728
01:16:50,550 --> 01:16:52,210
How many bodies?

729
01:16:52,230 --> 01:16:54,400
Birte Becker and Ms. Dahl.

730
01:16:54,430 --> 01:16:55,640
Where's Katrine?

731
01:16:55,670 --> 01:16:56,720
Suspended.

732
01:16:56,730 --> 01:16:59,040
She got a call telling her
they traced the Becker phone

733
01:16:59,060 --> 01:17:00,990
and didn't think to tell anyone.

734
01:17:01,030 --> 01:17:03,170
I asked you where she was.

735
01:17:03,200 --> 01:17:05,020
That's not my problem right now.

736
01:17:05,780 --> 01:17:07,880
He shot himself straight on.

737
01:17:09,360 --> 01:17:10,970
How'd he do that with a shotgun?

738
01:17:11,000 --> 01:17:13,660
It's too long, you have to angle it.

739
01:17:14,250 --> 01:17:16,770
Pellet marks should be
up there somewhere.

740
01:17:16,770 --> 01:17:19,940
Luckily, we have experts
to determine that.

741
01:17:22,220 --> 01:17:23,880
You sure he was alone?

742
01:17:23,900 --> 01:17:26,890
The garage door was closed.
One set of footprints.

743
01:17:26,890 --> 01:17:30,680
We found two bodies in the house
and Birte Becker's phone.

744
01:17:32,490 --> 01:17:34,340
It was a suicide.

745
01:17:34,490 --> 01:17:36,200
Case closed.

746
01:17:42,250 --> 01:17:45,730
Mathias, listen,
I have no idea where he's gone.

747
01:17:47,360 --> 01:17:50,110
Yes, I've checked my messages,
he hasn't called.

748
01:17:50,430 --> 01:17:54,590
Oh, well, how can you help?
You're at your bloody conference!

749
01:17:56,190 --> 01:17:57,860
Can I keep this?

750
01:17:58,690 --> 01:18:00,340
Can I keep this?

751
01:18:02,800 --> 01:18:04,010
Yeah, sure.

752
01:18:10,480 --> 01:18:12,380
She's not picking up.

753
01:18:20,630 --> 01:18:22,410
Katrine!

754
01:18:42,890 --> 01:18:44,590
Get off me!

755
01:18:47,210 --> 01:18:48,590
Stop.

756
01:18:56,010 --> 01:18:58,950
I guess congratulations are in order.

757
01:18:59,380 --> 01:19:04,980
You know it wasn't that creep.
Vetlesen didn't commit suicide.

758
01:19:05,380 --> 01:19:08,780
Someone killed him because
we got too close.

759
01:19:16,160 --> 01:19:18,080
Like your father.

760
01:19:19,380 --> 01:19:22,060
My father would never have
committed suicide.

761
01:19:22,250 --> 01:19:24,800
He would never have
left me like that.

762
01:19:24,900 --> 01:19:26,080
Get off me.

763
01:19:26,110 --> 01:19:27,830
Get off me, get off me!

764
01:19:27,860 --> 01:19:29,040
Get off me!

765
01:19:29,090 --> 01:19:31,890
Get off me you fucking drunk!

766
01:19:31,970 --> 01:19:33,190
Get off.

767
01:19:33,870 --> 01:19:35,150
Get off.

768
01:19:35,630 --> 01:19:37,250
Yeah.

769
01:19:38,720 --> 01:19:40,530
I'm a drunk.

770
01:19:44,530 --> 01:19:46,620
Like your father.

771
01:20:03,110 --> 01:20:05,510
Laila Aasen and Arve Stop
were having an affair...

772
01:20:05,530 --> 01:20:09,220
and that's the last thing my father
was investigating before he got killed.

773
01:20:11,580 --> 01:20:13,490
You broke in to Vetlesen's house

774
01:20:13,520 --> 01:20:16,120
because you were afraid
I'd find out this was personal

775
01:20:16,140 --> 01:20:17,510
and take you off the case.

776
01:20:17,540 --> 01:20:19,210
Vetlesen was his pimp.

777
01:20:19,240 --> 01:20:21,530
And they were both in Bergen
when the murders started.

778
01:20:21,560 --> 01:20:25,270
I know how much you want this,
but you can't force the pieces to fit.

779
01:20:25,270 --> 01:20:28,560
I called the Gellion clinic
and Vetlesen wasn't even working

780
01:20:28,560 --> 01:20:30,840
the day he was supposed
to meet Birte Becker.

781
01:20:31,880 --> 01:20:35,170
They found two dead bodies in his
house and Birte Becker's phone.

782
01:20:35,170 --> 01:20:36,550
Isn't that convenient, then?

783
01:20:36,640 --> 01:20:39,090
So Hagen has his killer
and Arve Stop's safe.

784
01:20:39,120 --> 01:20:40,620
And no questions are asked.

