to give him those pills?

950
01:39:10,830 --> 01:39:12,180
He didn't.

951
01:39:14,060 --> 01:39:15,990
You didn't have to do it for me.

952
01:39:16,230 --> 01:39:17,980
I didn't do it for you.

953
01:39:28,130 --> 01:39:30,110
It was never about you.

954
01:39:43,520 --> 01:39:45,740
I'm outside his house.

955
01:39:45,770 --> 01:39:48,740
I can't reach Rakel.
Send someone to her apartment.

956
01:40:13,510 --> 01:40:14,590
Oleg.

957
01:40:14,820 --> 01:40:16,550
Sorry to keep you waiting.

958
01:40:36,870 --> 01:40:39,160
Why do you have Mom's phone?

959
01:40:43,110 --> 01:40:44,230
Come on.

960
01:41:00,180 --> 01:41:02,530
You and I have more
in common than you think.

961
01:41:05,590 --> 01:41:08,220
I didn't know who
my father was either.

962
01:41:26,390 --> 01:41:28,830
Magnus, track Rakel's phone.

963
01:41:39,720 --> 01:41:41,350
Sorry, I...

964
01:41:46,680 --> 01:41:47,940
All right.

965
01:41:49,570 --> 01:41:51,840
Okay, Harry, we just
picked up a signal.

966
01:41:51,870 --> 01:41:53,540
Heading west towards Telemark.

967
01:41:53,570 --> 01:41:58,270
It is a red Volvo, registered to a
Mathias Lund-Helgesen...

968
01:41:58,270 --> 01:42:00,280
Rjukan, 2421.

969
01:42:02,610 --> 01:42:04,160
<i>The house is pretty remote.</i>

970
01:42:04,160 --> 01:42:06,300
There-there's an access
road, but that's it.

971
01:42:06,320 --> 01:42:07,970
And there's a big
lake around it.

972
01:42:08,820 --> 01:42:10,830
Helicopters are grounded
because of the weather.

973
01:42:10,850 --> 01:42:12,300
But Delta is on their way.

974
01:42:15,090 --> 01:42:17,180
Anything on Mathias' family?

975
01:42:17,210 --> 01:42:18,500
<i>Okay, I've got something here.</i>

976
01:42:18,500 --> 01:42:23,010
Jonas Lund-Helgesen, former
police officer, lost his job in '89.

977
01:42:23,430 --> 01:42:26,770
A scandal involving
a woman drowning in a car.

978
01:42:26,850 --> 01:42:28,240
Probable suicide.

979
01:42:28,260 --> 01:42:30,330
<i>She had a son.</i>

980
01:42:30,360 --> 01:42:31,100
Stop!

981
01:42:31,190 --> 01:42:32,850
<i>Father, unknown.</i>

982
01:42:32,880 --> 01:42:33,830
Please!

983
01:42:33,830 --> 01:42:35,900
<i>He was sent to an orphanage.</i>

984
01:42:43,770 --> 01:42:46,280
Who led the investigation
into the woman's disappearance?

985
01:42:46,950 --> 01:42:49,660
<i>Some local talent in village nearby.</i>

986
01:42:49,750 --> 01:42:51,000
<i>What's his name?</i>

987
01:42:51,030 --> 01:42:53,170
Jonas Lund-Helgesen.

988
01:42:54,170 --> 01:42:57,970
Jonas. No.
Please, stop!

989
01:43:18,030 --> 01:43:19,080
Harry?

990
01:43:19,460 --> 01:43:20,560
Harry!

991
01:43:20,600 --> 01:43:21,950
We've lost him.

992
01:45:19,520 --> 01:45:21,520
Sit down, Harry.

993
01:45:32,830 --> 01:45:34,200
Pass me the gun.

994
01:45:44,210 --> 01:45:46,300
I didn't think you'd find me.

995
01:45:48,720 --> 01:45:51,820
Perhaps the pills helped after all.

996
01:45:53,970 --> 01:45:56,640
I spoke to Filip Becker.

997
01:45:59,630 --> 01:46:01,380
What's going to happen

998
01:46:01,410 --> 01:46:04,630
when Josephine Becker finds out
he isn't her father?

999
01:46:07,020 --> 01:46:08,940
She'll still love him.

1000
01:46:09,190 --> 01:46:10,490
Wrong answer.

1001
01:46:21,040 --> 01:46:22,400
Let's try again.

1002
01:46:24,490 --> 01:46:28,350
Was it right for Sylvia Ottersen
to kill her unborn child...

1003
01:46:28,830 --> 01:46:32,350
simply because she couldn't
keep track of who the father was?

1004
01:46:34,760 --> 01:46:36,910
That was her choice.

1005
01:46:39,540 --> 01:46:41,080
Too short.

1006
01:46:41,370 --> 01:46:43,120
Maybe she was afraid.

1007
01:46:46,940 --> 01:46:49,100
What about you, Harry?

1008
01:46:50,730 --> 01:46:52,860
You have a woman who loves you.

1009
01:46:53,750 --> 01:46:55,670
A boy who's devoted to you.

1010
01:46:57,240 --> 01:46:59,380
Why did you abandon them?

1011
01:47:02,020 --> 01:47:03,900
They deserve better.

1012
01:47:06,350 --> 01:47:07,660
Too easy.

1013
01:47:08,870 --> 01:47:11,590
Because I'm selfish.

1014
01:47:14,920 --> 01:47:16,570
I'm an addict.

1015
01:47:19,680 --> 01:47:22,330
There isn't enough room for them.

1016
01:47:38,650 --> 01:47:42,150
You know, when I first saw
your picture in the papers...

1017
01:47:43,820 --> 01:47:45,850
with all those medals...

1018
01:47:47,330 --> 01:47:51,930
I thought, "That man
must have a perfect family."

1019
01:47:57,800 --> 01:47:59,500
And here you are.

1020
01:48:01,820 --> 01:48:03,680
Last question.

1021
01:48:04,550 --> 01:48:06,150
This boy...

1022
01:48:06,970 --> 01:48:09,360
who doesn't even know
who his father is...

1023
01:48:10,640 --> 01:48:13,630
who's had to put up with
so many men like you and me...

1024
01:48:13,650 --> 01:48:15,430
taking his place.

1025
01:48:19,440 --> 01:48:21,980
Does his mother deserve to live?

1026
01:48:26,030 --> 01:48:28,910
Why don't you ask him?

1027
01:49:12,910 --> 01:49:14,580
You all right?

1028
01:49:17,960 --> 01:49:19,160
Kill him.

1029
01:49:19,750 --> 01:49:20,860
Kill him.

1030
01:49:21,880 --> 01:49:23,170
Kill him!

1031
01:49:59,660 --> 01:50:01,090
Come on!

1032
01:50:02,420 --> 01:50:03,960
I'm ready!

1033
01:50:05,130 --> 01:50:06,610
I'm here!

1034
01:50:07,140 --> 01:50:08,790
Come on!

1035
01:50:41,030 --> 01:50:43,240
I know why you blame her.

1036
01:50:52,860 --> 01:50:56,460
You've been wrong
the whole time.

1037
01:51:02,660 --> 01:51:04,400
It wasn't her.

1038
01:51:10,380 --> 01:51:13,080
It wasn't you mother
who didn't want you.

1039
01:51:15,820 --> 01:51:17,630
<i>It was your father.</i>

1040
01:51:21,070 --> 01:51:23,870
It would have been better for him...

1041
01:51:27,040 --> 01:51:28,790
had you not been born.

